<\li1>
	* Capacity Development in Climate Change.

The specific objectives of the programme are:
* To improve soil fertility and land use management in key areas in Malawi;
* To enhance sustainable irrigation farming systems in selected districts prone to climate change effects;
* To promote climate change  adaptive agricultural technologies targeting climate change prone areas; and
* To increase household income through sustainable agricultural diversification in selected districts prone to climate change.

The specific objectives of the programme are:
* To develop transport infrastructure that will withstand climate change impacts;
* To improve telecommunication infrastructure stability in light of climate change;
* To increase energy infrastructure stability in light of climate change; and
* To improve sanitation infrastructure to deal with health challenges that arise as a result of climate change.

The specific objectives of the programme include:
* To enhance mainstreaming of climate change related disaster risk management in all sectoral planning processes in Malawi;
* To improve disaster risk management information system in the various sectors in Malawi;
* To improve community based early warning system for various sectoral development programmes and projects; and
* To strengthen preparedness capacity for effective response and recovery at all levels in Malawi.

The specific objectives of the programme are as follows:
* To increase area under afforestation and reforestation;
* Reduce the area under bushfires in order to curb emissions as well as to allow the transplanted seedlings to grow;
* To improve livelihoods of communities who rely on forest and non-forest products; and
* To promote and regulate REDD+ activities.

The specific objectives of the programme are:
* To reduce emission of green house gases;
* To reduce the negative effects of the changing climate on energy development;
* To promote energy efficient technologies among the urban and rural communities in Malawi;
* To introduce alternative brick making technologies from the burnt bricks; and
* To facilitate rural electrification for rural communities.
